{
  "stem": "2170.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Whatever we had, we put everything on the table and they were very happy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then, she was-- she had a mother, her mother was a doctor, and she came home later.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And her father was [NON-ENGLISH] in the Red Army.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then I told her my purpose coming to Moscow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And when I told her, she got scared.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She couldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But she said that my mother will take you to the American embassy tomorrow and show you where it is, and you go in yourself.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I was very happy that she told me this, but then in the-- in the morning, we hear that there's gonna be a holiday that Eisenhower is coming in to Moscow to greet after the Second World War.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And there was a special day to meet with Stalin, and we come close to the station, they tell us that it was all circled with the Russian police.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We were not allowed to go into the center because I had to go to the American embassy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It is right near the Red Square.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "This was [INAUDIBLE] square of [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So we went back the other day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "She took me to the American embassy, and she-- we went out to the station.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And she showed me where the American embassy is.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And just you walk yourself.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As I came close, I saw two policeman standing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I came over, and I said, I would like to go into the American embassy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they just told me, go straight to the right, make a right, and there is the American embassy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I thought maybe they will arrest me, I thought what is a-- a Russian citizen doing there?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But somehow God was with me and I got in.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
